	<p><h2>Toxins in our lives</h2></p>
		<ul>The problem is so embedded in our lives that <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/29/opinion/sunday/contaminating-our-bodies-with-everyday-products.html?_r=2" target="_blank">babies</a> are being born with pollutants in their system.</ul>
		<ul>Here is a story about a beauty <a href="http://www.womensvoices.org/2016/02/09/moiras-story-fragrance-formaldehyde/" target="_blank">salon</a></ul>	
 		<ul>Johnson & Johnson is going to stop putting <a href="http://www.healthyfoodhouse.com/johnson-johnson-admits-our-baby-products-contain-cancer-causing-formaldehyde/" target="_blank">formaldehyde</a> from 100's of their products including baby products.</ul>
   	<ul>Are manufacturers disclosing enough about their <a href="http://www.womensvoices.org/2016/02/12/questions-raised-about-sc-johnsons-commitment-to-transparency/" target="_blank">products?</a></ul>
   	<ul>There are those of us who are injured by fragrances but there are <a href="https://multiplechemicalsensitivity.wordpress.com/2015/12/30/obsessive-fragrance-wearers/" target="_blank">others</a> who are apparently addicted to them.</ul>
